The paper is about learning to rank, which is a subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of deep neural networks suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) category. The paper also deals with the ambiguity of relevance labels, which is a common issue in natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the proposed method involves sampling techniques, which is a common approach in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
